Sentencas: A dense La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) film is fabricated using the pulsed laser deposition (PLO) technique on a Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC) electrolyte which is prepared using a co-pressing process on a NiO -SDC anode substrate.
Titulo: Improved performance of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cell using doped LaGaO3 films deposited by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The LSGM/SDC bilayer electrolyte cell with Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta-Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SSC -SDC, 70:30 wt.%) cathode achieves significantly enhanced cell performance, yielding open circuit voltage (OCV) value of 0.89 V and maximum power density of 758 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Improved performance of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cell using doped LaGaO3 films deposited by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The electrical current leakage in the SDC single layer cell caused by the reduction of Ce4+ to Ce3+ in reducing environment has been eliminated by depositing the LSGM thin film as a blocking layer; besides, the reaction between NiO and LSGM can be prevented due to the dense SDC electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Improved performance of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cell using doped LaGaO3 films deposited by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: The influence of oxygen pressure and post-annealing temperature on the crystallinity, microstructure and surface roughness of the LSGM films are studied for obtaining a high quality film.
Titulo: Improved performance of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cell using doped LaGaO3 films deposited by pulsed laser deposition

Sentencas: Characterization analysis of the cell shows that the bilayer electrolyte deposited by the PLD technique have retained the chemical, mechanical and structural integrity of the cell.
Titulo: Improved performance of ceria-based solid oxide fuel cell using doped LaGaO3 films deposited by pulsed laser deposition
